                <h2 class="author-name">About Viktor Frankl</h2>
                <p class="author-description">An Austrian neurologist, psychiatrist, and Holocaust survivor whose experiences profoundly shaped his career as an author. His most famous work, <strong style="font-weight: bold;">"Man's Search for Meaning,"</strong> combines his personal narrative of enduring life in Nazi concentration camps with insights from his psychological practice. The book emphasizes the importance of finding purpose, even in the most challenging circumstances. Frankl argues that meaning is essential for psychological well-being and introduces logotherapy, his therapeutic approach focused on helping individuals discover personal significance in their lives. Through his reflections, Frankl inspires readers to confront suffering with resilience and hope.</p>
