                <h2 class="author-name">About Stan Lee</h2>
                <p class="author-description">Known for co-creating legendary characters like Spider-Man, Stan Lee was a significant writer and editor for comic books. In "The Amazing Spider-Man," illustrator Steve Ditko and writer Stan Lee narrate the tale of teenage Peter Parker, who acquires superpowers following a radioactive spider bite. The Green Goblin and other well-known villains test Peter's ability to balance his personal life with his heroic obligations as Spider-Man. The story focuses on themes of justice, identity, and accountability; the well-known quote, "With great power comes great responsibility," captures these ideas and makes Spider-Man a timeless and approachable hero.</p>
